{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:41:17.558Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NumPy vectorization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the technique of applying operations on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "entire arrays at once"}, {"type": "text", "text": " without using explicit Python loops, leveraging fast C/C++ implementations internally to make numerical computations 10–1000x faster than manual iteration."}]}, {"type": "blockquote", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Simple definition:"}, {"type": "text", "text": " “Vectorization in NumPy refers to applying operations on entire arrays without using explicit loops. These operations are "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "internally optimized using fast C/C++ implementations"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", making numerical computations more efficient and easier to write.”"}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "NumPy Vectorization — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What vectorization means"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Python, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "loops are slow"}, {"type": "text", "text": " because they run line-by-line in Python. In contrast, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vectorized operations"}, {"type": "text", "text": " run in optimized C code, applying the same instruction to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "all elements in one moment"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Adding a number to an array"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Vectorized operation (no loop)\narr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])\nresult = arr + 10  # Adds 10 to each element automatically\n\nprint(result)  # [11, 12, 13, 14, 15]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NumPy automatically adds 10 to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "every element"}, {"type": "text", "text": " without you writing a loop."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why vectorization is faster"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vectorization is NumPy's "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "most important performance optimization"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". It works because:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Python Loops"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NumPy Vectorization"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Execution"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Line-by-line in Python (slow)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Optimized C code internally (fast)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Instruction pattern"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "One instruction per element"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SIMD"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Single Instruction Multiple Data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Memory access"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Individual element access"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Array-level access (efficient)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Speedup"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Baseline"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "10–1000x faster"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SIMD (Single Instruction Multiple Data)"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": NumPy applies one instruction to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "any number of data elements per one moment in time"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to produce multiple results."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common vectorization techniques in NumPy"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Element-wise operations"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Apply operations to each element automatically:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\narr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])\n\n# Vectorized arithmetic\nresult = arr * 2 + 3  # [5, 7, 9, 11, 13]\n\n# Vectorized math functions\nresult = np.sqrt(arr)  # [1.0, 1.414, 1.732, 2.0, 2.236]\nresult = np.exp(arr)   # [2.718, 7.389, 20.086, 54.598, 148.413]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Every mathematical operation with arrays is automatically vectorized"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in NumPy."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Broadcasting"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Apply operations between arrays of different shapes:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\n# Array + scalar\narr = np.array([1, 2, 3])\nresult = arr + 10  # [11, 12, 13]\n\n# Array + smaller array (broadcasting)\narr1 = np.array([[1, 2, 3], [4, 5, 6]])\narr2 = np.array([10, 20, 30])\nresult = arr1 + arr2  # [[11, 22, 33], [14, 25, 36]]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Broadcasting allows NumPy to apply operations across arrays with compatible shapes without explicit loops."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Array-to-array operations"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Add, multiply, or compare two arrays element-wise:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\narr1 = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])\narr2 = np.array([10, 20, 30, 40, 50])\n\n# Vectorized addition\nresult = arr1 + arr2  # [11, 22, 33, 44, 55]\n\n# Vectorized multiplication\nresult = arr1 * arr2  # [10, 40, 90, 160, 250]\n\n# Vectorized comparison\nresult = arr1 > arr2  # [False, False, False, False, False]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "This is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vectorized operation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " where corresponding elements of two arrays are added together element-wise."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "4. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reductions (aggregations)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Compute statistics over entire arrays:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\narr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])\n\n# Vectorized reductions\nmean = np.mean(arr)     # 3.0\nstd = np.std(arr)       # 1.581\nsum = np.sum(arr)       # 15\nmax = np.max(arr)       # 5\nmin = np.min(arr)       # 1"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "These operations run in C and are much faster than Python loops."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "5. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Vectorized conditional operations with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "np.where"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Replace slow iteration with vectorized conditionals:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\nimport pandas as pd\n\n# ❌ Slow way (iteration)\ndf = pd.DataFrame({'score': [85, 92, 78, 95, 70]})\n\ndef calculate_grade(row):\n    if row['score'] > 90:\n        return 'A'\n    elif row['score'] > 80:\n        return 'B'\n    elif row['score'] > 70:\n        return 'C'\n    else:\n        return 'F'\n\ndf['grade'] = df.apply(calculate_grade, axis=1)  # Slow"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "✅ Fast way (vectorization with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "np.where"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": ")"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "df['grade'] = np.where(\n    df['score'] > 90, 'A',\n    np.where(df['score'] > 80, 'B',\n    np.where(df['score'] > 70, 'C', 'F'))\n)\n# Same result, but runs in seconds even on millions of rows [web:155]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For 2+ conditions, use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.select"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "conditions = [\n    df['score'] > 90,\n    df['score'] > 80,\n    df['score'] > 70\n]\nchoices = ['A', 'B', 'C']\ndf['grade'] = np.select(conditions, choices, default='F')"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "6. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Universal functions (ufuncs)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NumPy's built-in vectorized functions:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\n\narr = np.array([1, 2, 3, 4, 5])\n\n# Ufuncs (all vectorized)\nresult = np.add(arr, 10)      # [11, 12, 13, 14, 15]\nresult = np.multiply(arr, 2)  # [2, 4, 6, 8, 10]\nresult = np.maximum(arr, 3)   # [3, 3, 3, 4, 5]\nresult = np.sin(arr)          # [0.841, 0.909, 0.141, -0.757, -0.959]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Chain ufuncs"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "out="}, {"type": "text", "text": " / "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "where="}, {"type": "text", "text": " to reduce temporaries."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "7. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Advanced vectorization moves"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "For complex data pipelines, use these proven patterns:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Technique"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What it does"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Masks"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Boolean indexing: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "arr[arr > 0]"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "ufuncs"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast vectorized functions (e.g., "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.maximum"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.sin"}, {"type": "text", "text": ")"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "einsum"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Efficient tensor operations (e.g., matrix multiplication)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sliding windows"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Apply operations over windows (e.g., moving average)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "argpartition"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Efficient partial sorting"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "bincount"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Fast histogram/counting"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vectorization in NumPy vs. pandas"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Aspect"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "NumPy"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "pandas"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best for"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Numerical calculations, fast array operations"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Data analysis, visualization, labeled data"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Vectorization speed"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Faster (direct C implementation)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Slightly slower but still fast"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data structure"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "ndarray"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (unlabeled)"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "DataFrame"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (with indices, columns)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Use case"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "ML pipelines, numerical computation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Data exploration, cleaning, transformation"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Best practice"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "pandas for loading and cleaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", then convert to "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NumPy arrays for ML"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Performance comparison: loops vs. vectorization"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "import numpy as np\nimport time\n\n# Create large array\narr = np.random.rand(1_000_000)\n\n# ❌ Slow: Python loop\nstart = time.time()\nresult_loop = np.zeros(len(arr))\nfor i in range(len(arr)):\n    result_loop[i] = arr[i] * 2 + 3\nloop_time = time.time() - start\n\n# ✅ Fast: Vectorization\nstart = time.time()\nresult_vec = arr * 2 + 3\nvec_time = time.time() - start\n\nprint(f\"Loop time: {loop_time:.4f}s\")\nprint(f\"Vector time: {vec_time:.4f}s\")\nprint(f\"Speedup: {loop_time / vec_time:.1f}x\")"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Result"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Vectorization is typically "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "10–100x faster"}, {"type": "text", "text": " on 1M rows."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Best practices for NumPy vectorization"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Prefer views over copies"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Many NumPy operations return a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "view"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (fast, memory-light):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# View (fast)\narr_view = arr[::2]  # Slices return views\n\n# Copy if needed\narr_copy = arr.copy()"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "If converting types, try "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "astype(new_dtype, copy=False)"}, {"type": "text", "text": " to avoid unnecessary copies."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Chain ufuncs and reduce temporaries"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# Efficient: chain ufuncs\nresult = np.add(np.multiply(arr, 2), 3)\n\n# With out= to reduce temporaries\nresult = np.add(np.multiply(arr, 2), 3, out=np.empty_like(arr))"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Measure with realistic shapes"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A trick that's 10× faster on 1e6 rows can be slower on 1e3. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Benchmark with your actual data size"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "✅ Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.where"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for 1 condition, "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.select"}, {"type": "text", "text": " for 2+"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "python"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "# 1 condition: np.where\nresult = np.where(arr > 0, arr, 0)\n\n# 2+ conditions: np.select\nconditions = [arr > 10, arr > 5, arr > 0]\nchoices = [3, 2, 1]\nresult = np.select(conditions, choices, default=0)"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "NumPy vectorization"}, {"type": "text", "text": " applies operations on "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "entire arrays at once"}, {"type": "text", "text": " without explicit loops, using fast C/C++ implementations."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Vectorization is "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "10–1000x faster"}, {"type": "text", "text": " than Python loops because it runs in optimized C code with "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "SIMD"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (Single Instruction Multiple Data)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Every mathematical operation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " with arrays is automatically vectorized in NumPy (no need to call "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "vectorize()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " always)."}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Common techniques:"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Element-wise ops"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "arr 2 + 3"}, {"type": "text", "text": " - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Broadcasting"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Array + scalar, array + smaller array - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Reductions"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.mean()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.sum()"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "code"}], "text": "np.std()"}, {"type": "text", "text": " - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "np.where"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Vectorized conditionals for 1 condition - "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}, {"type": "code"}], "text": "np.select"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Vectorized conditionals for 2+ conditions\n- Use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "views over copies"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", chain ufuncs, reduce temporaries, and benchmark with realistic data sizes.\n- In data pipelines: "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "load/clean with pandas"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "convert to NumPy"}, {"type": "text", "text": " → "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "vectorize for ML"}, {"type": "text", "text": "."}]}]}}